For simplicity, I will assume that the following events occur simultaneously at timeT: (i) the futures contract stops trading, (ii) the last settlement price becomes known, (iii) the short chooses the bond to deliver, (iv) the seller delivers, and (v) the buyer pays for the bond. In futures contracts on a single underlying bond, the short party receives the last settlement price
